/*


cp -r /var/www/Pembeni/custom-reports/* /var/www/quickflex/custom-reports/

cp -r /var/www/nwk_s2/lending/services/* /var/www/nwk_s2/lender/services/

1) Pulling From Github to Targeted Server:
- git remote add origin https://github.com/ngarama/super-lender.git
- git pull origin main

2) Remove Unwanted Files the following directories:
- custom-reports/*
- apis/* 
- extensions/* 

NB: Comman to use: 
-First navigate to project root directory e.g. cd /var/www/your_domain_name, then run the following command:
rm -rf apis/* custom-reports/* extensions/*

-Also you could copy existing files from another project as follows:
a) cp -r /var/www/tenakata/custom-reports/* /var/www/Pembeni/custom-reports/
b) cp -r /var/www/tenakata/apis/* /var/www/Pembeni/apis/
c) cp -r /var/www/tenakata/extensions/* /var/www/Pembeni/extensions/

3) Create the following directories:
- configs
- uploads_
- uploads_/original
- airtel-uploads
- mpesa_uploads
- assets-upload
- campaign_uploads


- copying from another project use the following command:
rsync -av --exclude='uploads_' --exclude='uploads_/original' --exclude='airtel-uploads' --exclude='mpesa_uploads' --exclude='assets-upload' --exclude='campaign_uploads' /opt/lampp/htdocs/super-lender/ //opt/lampp/htdocs/super-lender-backup/

- Command to use to creating excluded above list of directories at a go:
mkdir -p /var/www/Pembeni/configs /var/www/Pembeni/uploads_{,original} /var/www/Pembeni/{airtel,mpesa,assets}_uploads /var/www/Pembeni/campaign_uploads

- This command uses the -p option to create parent directories if they do not exist. 

- The curly braces {} are used for brace expansion, allowing you to create multiple directories in a single command.


4) Push the following files from localhost:
- configs/conn.inc: adjust credentials them accordingly. Or copy existing using command: cp -r /var/www/tenakata/configs/* /var/www/Pembeni/configs/
- bower_components
- dist
- build
- documentation
- test.php

Use the following to copy the above files from another project:
mkdir -p /var/www/Pembeni/configs
cp -r /var/www/tenakata/configs/* /var/www/Pembeni/configs/

mkdir -p /var/www/Pembeni/bower_components
cp -r /var/www/tenakata/bower_components /var/www/Pembeni/

mkdir -p /var/www/Pembeni/dist
cp -r /var/www/tenakata/dist /var/www/Pembeni/

mkdir -p /var/www/Pembeni/build
cp -r /var/www/tenakata/build /var/www/Pembeni/

mkdir -p /var/www/Pembeni/documentation
cp -r /var/www/tenakata/documentation /var/www/Pembeni/



# db schema from another project
mysqldump -u username -p --no-data databasename > /var/www/Pembeni/Pembeni.sql

